   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Collective bargaining on real improvements: Trade unions and companies will have concluded Collective bargaining Agreements (CBAs) on real improvement of labour conditions and the Decent Work Agenda (DO2).</narrative>
   </title>
   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">For example In 2019, the industry unions affiliated to the Federation of Food, Beverages and Allied Workers (ABA) and the Federation of Workers in the Manufacturing Industry and Related Services of Peru (FETRIMAP), managed to sign 20 collective bargaining agreements that benefited 6,015 members, 1,369 of whom are women, but as the companies extended the improvements in working conditions to all of their workers, the total number of benefited workers was 30,084.</narrative>
