  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Trade unions effectively influence agenda of government (BC1)</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="1" measure="2">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of Social Dialogue meetings where TU supported proposal was discussed with government</narrative>
    </title>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <actual value="8">
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the context of the pandemic, the CGTP adequately combined the strategies of mobilisation and dialogue, to face a set of wrong government decisions that aggravated the effects of the pandemic, on health and employment, achieving the result that three of their proposals were accepted. The initiatives were developed in two ways, on the one hand, the preparation of legal proposals based on analysis studies, on the other the establishment of coordinated union action agreements that opened the way for a series of advocacy mobilisations throughout the year. In the process of preparing the proposal on the strengthening of the health and safety committees, the information shared by companies and union members was incorporated in forums organised by the Association for Work (bipartite dialogue entity) on good practices of social dialogue to face the pandemic in the workplace. Subsequently, the proposal was presented and approved by the National Council for Occupational Safety and Health, which is a tripartite entity.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
